<font color="#FF0000">VIETNAM!!</font><br>
<tt>Sun Apr  6  9:17:28 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Art,<br><br>
Very, Very well written! My sentiments exactly.<br><br>
I have moved on to better things and consider myself successful in the little town where I live - even though I am a &quot;small potatoes&quot; painting and paperhanging contractor. My phone rings all the time and I barely can keep up with business. I am not &quot;stuck&quot; in the throes of Vietnam. I manage quite well. I know contentment in life. There is no putting $ signs on contentment. <br><br>
MY PURPOSE of discussing Vietnam on the www, however, is to &quot;further the understanding&quot; of the war even though it ended many years ago. I do this by creating (with the help of my son) and maintaining a website whose topic is the war in Vietnam. I get requests almost daily for more information from students, housewives, and college professors. Always the words from fellow vets have been of encouragement. I save all messages that pertain to my site, btw, as a reminder that my work is worthwhile and good.<br><br>
To say to my fellow vets to forget the war ever happened would be telling them to do the impossible. <br><br>
Rather, I would say: use this wonderful medium of the Internet to express yourself. Express yourself in any manner - let the vitriol fly, even! We are out here listening and understanding.<br><br>
Love and Peace,<br><br>
Tom<br><br>

